content:
Of the 23 games played between the Kansas City Chiefs and the Jacksonville Jaguars, 12 games were played at Arrowhead Stadium in Kansas City, Missouri, which is the home stadium of the Kansas City Chiefs. The remaining 11 games were played at TIAA Bank Field, Jacksonville, Florida, which is the home stadium of the Jacksonville Jaguars.
It is worth mentioning that these statistics are based on regular season games only, not including playoffs games.
